15:51.433 --> 15:54.470
Um, some might call me
a collector.

15:54.574 --> 15:58.267
But there is one obsession
in particular

15:58.371 --> 16:00.476
that has held me captive.

16:01.650 --> 16:03.134
The Crown of Fire

16:03.238 --> 16:05.619
and its cascading
red diamonds.

16:05.723 --> 16:09.382
Is this a... Is this
a hidden-camera thing?

16:09.485 --> 16:13.075
So imagine my surprise
when, in your new book,

16:13.179 --> 16:16.458
amidst the pages
of coital reverie,

16:16.561 --> 16:17.390
was something...

16:17.493 --> 16:19.564
Oh, God....quite magnificent.

16:21.428 --> 16:23.983
I get it. I get it.
I so get it right now.

16:24.086 --> 16:25.398
Oh, my gosh.

16:25.501 --> 16:27.676
I literally thought
you guys kidnapped me.

16:27.779 --> 16:30.265
I mean,
this is marketing, right?
Beth set this up?

16:30.368 --> 16:33.268
This was so good, you guys.
This was amazing.

16:33.371 --> 16:36.616
You, with your gun
and your mustache

16:36.719 --> 16:39.688
and your,
"You'd better get in there"
and you know...

16:40.896 --> 16:42.415
Oh, my God.

16:42.518 --> 16:46.281
You, with the G.I. Joe
tone-on-tone outfit.

16:46.384 --> 16:51.389
Your fictional archaeologist
was making real translations
of a dead language.

16:51.493 --> 16:54.392
Mm-hmm.Something nobody else
has been able to do.

16:54.496 --> 16:56.912
Well, nobody else
had ever tried.

16:57.016 --> 16:58.845
Is that right?
Am I saying the right thing?

16:58.948 --> 17:00.605
Except you, right?

17:00.709 --> 17:02.676
Except me!

17:02.780 --> 17:04.506
Yes. See, it turns out

17:04.609 --> 17:07.923
Loretta Sage
was once a young college girl
doing her dissertation

17:08.027 --> 17:10.891
on the dead language of the D
with her future husband,

17:10.995 --> 17:14.102
dreaming
of finding Kalaman's tomb
and the Crown of Fire.

17:14.205 --> 17:17.312
I was sorry to read
you gave up your search
after he died.

17:17.415 --> 17:19.038
But what that means is,

17:20.315 --> 17:22.213
you're all I have left.

17:22.317 --> 17:25.492
All-All you have left
for... what?

17:25.596 --> 17:26.631
Hmm.

17:28.426 --> 17:29.669
Oh.

17:29.772 --> 17:31.153
Here we go.

17:45.271 --> 17:46.996
What is this?

17:47.100 --> 17:50.793
I believe it is describing
the exact location
of Kalaman's tomb,

17:50.897 --> 17:54.349
in which Taha
and her priceless headdress
are buried.

17:54.452 --> 17:56.592
Well, if this were authentic,

17:56.696 --> 18:02.046
you would still have to
uncover an entire city

18:02.150 --> 18:05.187
that nobody
has been able to find.

18:05.291 --> 18:06.947
I found it.

18:07.051 --> 18:10.192
On a tiny, forgotten island
in the Atlantic
called Isla Hundida.

18:10.296 --> 18:13.851
What I have not been
able to find is Kalaman's
final resting place.

18:13.954 --> 18:18.235
This piece of parchment
is the only clue we found
among the ruins.

18:18.338 --> 18:21.479
I need someone
who can decipher these symbols.

18:22.101 --> 18:23.654
I need you.

18:24.793 --> 18:26.243
Well...Miss Sage,

18:26.346 --> 18:29.729
surely this isn't how
you want your story to end.

18:29.832 --> 18:32.421
We both had our dreams crushed
by bad luck,

18:32.525 --> 18:34.768
or in my case,
an arse-kissing little brother,

18:34.872 --> 18:37.978
but this is our chance
to show them all.

18:38.082 --> 18:39.670
Come with me...
to the island.

18:39.773 --> 18:44.916
Translate these symbols
and help me find
the Crown of Fire.

18:45.020 --> 18:47.643
You can name your price.

18:50.267 --> 18:53.097
I must respectfully decline.

18:57.964 --> 18:59.172
Well...

19:00.794 --> 19:02.762
I can't say
I'm not disappointed.

19:03.659 --> 19:06.145
But I understand
how you feel.

19:09.493 --> 19:11.253
Will you at least let us
give you a ride?

19:11.357 --> 19:15.637
Oh, no, thank you.
I'll call for my own car,
and I'll just...

19:37.210 --> 19:40.972
I don't feel like
you're listening to me.
This is urgent, and we--

19:41.076 --> 19:44.010
Okay, so the police are saying
that they put out an APB...

19:44.113 --> 19:45.770
APB....on an SUV,

19:45.874 --> 19:48.117
and there's
this 24-hour rule...Why is there a rule?

19:48.221 --> 19:50.637
...and they won't
do anything until...What about the FBI or the CIA?

19:50.741 --> 19:52.708
-They said to call the police.
-I'm sure Loretta's fine.

19:52.812 --> 19:55.401
When I was in college,
my friend Nicki went missing.

19:55.504 --> 19:57.126
Everyone was, like,
freaking out.

19:57.230 --> 19:59.577
But then she was just
in her car.

19:59.681 --> 20:02.856
She was dead, but we found her.
She wasn't gone.

20:02.960 --> 20:07.309
Um, what about...
Maybe we could get a PI

20:07.413 --> 20:09.932
or, like, you know,
private security or--

20:10.036 --> 20:11.934
What about an extraction team,
like the movie?

20:12.038 --> 20:14.523
Yes! But who does that?
The ex-military, right?

20:14.627 --> 20:17.216
Oh, yeah. I think
I actually have somebody
that could help us.

20:17.319 --> 20:20.288
-Oh.
-I did this meditation retreat,

20:20.391 --> 20:22.462
and there was this
trainer guy there.

20:22.566 --> 20:24.084
You should
see this guy meditate.

20:24.188 --> 20:25.603
But he's ex-Navy SEAL.

20:25.707 --> 20:29.504
He-- He's a special ops trainer.
What was his name?

20:30.194 --> 20:31.333
Yeah. Jack Trainer.

20:31.437 --> 20:33.059
So he's a trainer
named Jack Trainer?

20:33.162 --> 20:35.337
That's how I have
everybody in my phone.
See, "Janice Mom."

20:35.441 --> 20:36.890
"Larry Doorknob."
"Stacy Butt Stuff."

20:36.994 --> 20:39.686
Look, this is
what this guy does.
He finds people.

20:39.790 --> 20:42.068
If there's anybody
that can help us, it's him.

20:49.006 --> 20:51.526
Jack Trainer.Oh, so his name
is actually Jack Trainer.

20:51.629 --> 20:55.530
Hi, uh, this is Alan
from "Touching Your Inner Self."

20:57.014 --> 20:58.843
The meditation retreat?

21:00.569 --> 21:03.641
Anyway, uh, okay.
Our friend Loretta
has been kidnapped,

21:03.745 --> 21:05.194
and no one's helping us.

21:05.298 --> 21:06.782
How long she been missing?

21:06.886 --> 21:08.128
Maybe two hours now.

21:08.232 --> 21:09.544
Who is that?

21:09.647 --> 21:13.686
Um, this is B--
This is Beth. I'm Beth.

21:13.789 --> 21:16.205
And Allison
is on too, sir.

21:16.309 --> 21:18.518
Did she have any
Wi-Fi-enabled devices?

21:18.622 --> 21:21.521
-She's got her phone, right?
-No, I have her phone.

21:21.625 --> 21:24.248
Oh! She has a smartwatch.
It ripped my wig off.

21:24.352 --> 21:27.286
What was that scenario?
Never mind. Open the phone.

21:27.389 --> 21:28.942
Go to the smartwatch app.All right.

21:29.046 --> 21:31.359
Then hit "Find My Smartwatch."

21:31.462 --> 21:34.396
Oh, my... That is so good.
That's why we called.

21:34.500 --> 21:36.950
"Anticipate the difficult
by managing the easy."

21:37.054 --> 21:40.747
Is that Oprah or Deepak? Laozi fromTao-te Ching.

21:40.851 --> 21:42.059
Oh, my God.

21:42.162 --> 21:43.854
It's in the Atlantic.

21:43.957 --> 21:46.305
She's on a plane?
How can you tell that?

21:46.408 --> 21:48.583
'Cause she can't swim
that fast.

21:48.686 --> 21:50.136
Doesn't sound like
a ransom scenario.

21:50.239 --> 21:52.863
My guess is blood sport,
Hunger Games type situation.

21:52.966 --> 21:55.797
Possibly some coke-fueled
dark web scavenger hunt.

21:55.900 --> 21:57.937
Real clown shit.
We'll have to move fast.

21:58.040 --> 22:00.974
-How do we pay you?
-Cryptocurrency. Cash App.

22:01.078 --> 22:04.564
I'll have her back
within 48 hours
or your next rescue is free.

22:04.668 --> 22:06.152
How many people
need a next rescue?

22:06.255 --> 22:07.774
More than you'd think.

22:07.878 --> 22:09.707
-I'm gonna need that phone.
-I'll bring it to you.

22:09.811 --> 22:12.572
Let me know where she lands.
I'll meet you there, Alan.

22:27.380 --> 22:28.623
Hello.

22:33.213 --> 22:34.353
Where am I?

22:34.456 --> 22:36.458
Um, you're on my plane.

22:36.562 --> 22:37.770
It's nice, isn't it? Hmm?

22:37.873 --> 22:39.703
The seats are made of
mama llama leather.

22:39.806 --> 22:42.913
Well, I'm getting off
your plane.

22:43.016 --> 22:44.397
Unchain me!

22:44.501 --> 22:46.054
That's your seat belt.

22:46.641 --> 22:48.505
Did you chloroform me?

22:48.608 --> 22:50.817
People actually do that?

22:53.199 --> 22:55.857
Well, you know,
it's a classic for a reason.

22:56.547 --> 22:57.790
My body feels drunk.

22:57.893 --> 22:59.792
It'll wear off in a bit.
I am sorry.

22:59.895 --> 23:02.311
I just couldn't wait around
for you to change your mind.

23:02.415 --> 23:04.866
Stop playing jelly.Time is not on our side.

23:04.969 --> 23:07.696
You see, the volcano
we're excavating around

23:07.800 --> 23:09.767
has developed
a bad case of indigestion.

23:09.871 --> 23:11.735
I'm rather worried
that when it blows,

23:11.838 --> 23:13.909
everything that's left
of the Lost City
will be destroyed.

23:14.013 --> 23:15.911
Oh, my God.
My legs don't work.

23:16.015 --> 23:21.434
So, this is our last chance
to find both the tomb
and the crown.

23:21.538 --> 23:23.574
Oh, God. Oh!

23:23.678 --> 23:25.956
Don't worry.
That's just our final descent.

23:26.059 --> 23:32.065
But it is the beginning
of the greatest adventure
of your life.

24:40.686 --> 24:42.757
Welcome to the Lost City.

24:52.387 --> 24:53.802
How did you find it?

24:53.906 --> 24:56.046
So, the city was built
on a lava dome.

24:56.149 --> 24:58.842
As the volcano became active,
the dome filled with lava,

24:58.945 --> 25:01.569
and sunken things
rose to the surface.

25:01.672 --> 25:03.571
The D exposed itself.

25:03.674 --> 25:06.712
-The entire city?
-No, no. Just the tip.

25:06.815 --> 25:10.025
As soon as I heard rumors
of the ruins, I flew over
and bought the place.

25:10.129 --> 25:13.408
The site?No. The island.
The southern half.

25:13.512 --> 25:15.859
I got a good deal
'cause this is where
the lava flows.

25:15.962 --> 25:18.206
We've been excavating
for a year now.

25:19.276 --> 25:21.830
One doesn't kidnap
a romance novelist
on day one.

25:21.934 --> 25:23.970
Ah, yes, as the saying goes.

25:24.074 --> 25:27.077
Rafi doesn't like it.
Do you, Rafi?

25:27.180 --> 25:30.356
He says
we're disrespecting
his heritage.

25:30.459 --> 25:33.704
But not a lot of other
job options on the island,
are there, Rafi?

25:33.808 --> 25:35.879
Beggars can't be choosers.

25:45.716 --> 25:47.546
No more charcuterie,
I take it.

25:47.649 --> 25:49.755
Mmm. Please.
I'm not a monster.

25:49.858 --> 25:51.688
Whatever you need, just shout.

25:53.206 --> 25:58.073
Uh, leave one hand free.
She has some translating to do.

25:59.281 --> 26:00.524
And then what?

26:00.628 --> 26:03.147
Loretta, I really wish
you would try and see

26:03.251 --> 26:05.391
what an exciting opportunity
this is for us.

26:05.494 --> 26:09.395
I believe this text describes
the exact location of the tomb.

26:09.498 --> 26:12.018
It's a logographic system.

26:12.778 --> 26:15.366
Like cuneiform or hieroglyphics.

26:15.470 --> 26:19.267
Now, if you have other documents
that possibly I can compare--

26:19.370 --> 26:20.648
Yeah, no luck there.

26:20.751 --> 26:23.547
We found some scratching
at a nearby waterfall,

26:23.651 --> 26:24.548
but it was useless.

26:24.652 --> 26:26.205
Just pictures of women.

26:26.308 --> 26:30.899
Look, I, too, wish
your dear old dead
archaeologist husband

26:31.003 --> 26:33.730
was here to help,
but he's not, so,

26:33.833 --> 26:36.940
time to shine, Loretta,
sex-book writer.

26:38.355 --> 26:40.081
They will come for me.

26:40.668 --> 26:42.393
Who, exactly?

26:42.497 --> 26:44.223
Your-- Your many cats?

26:44.326 --> 26:46.121
Oh, I don't have cats.

26:46.708 --> 26:48.537
Somehow even more sad.

26:48.641 --> 26:51.610
I have a hamster, asshole!

26:51.713 --> 26:53.370
You have a hamster's asshole?

26:53.473 --> 26:57.236
No, there was a--
there was a comma between--
Forget it.

26:57.339 --> 27:00.757
I bet your brother never had
to kidnap anyone!

27:32.478 --> 27:35.757
♪ From the dusty mesa♪

27:35.861 --> 27:40.175
♪ Her looming shadow grows♪

27:40.279 --> 27:43.662
♪ Hidden in the branches♪

27:43.765 --> 27:47.838
♪ Of the poison creosote♪

27:51.497 --> 27:53.085
Good to see you, man.

27:53.188 --> 27:54.811
Phone.Right.

28:06.685 --> 28:07.927
What?

28:08.031 --> 28:10.619
Yeah, I was thinking
that I could, you know,

28:10.723 --> 28:12.311
maybe just sort of
come with you.

28:12.414 --> 28:14.175
Why?To help.

28:14.278 --> 28:18.420
I know CPR.
I know some light karate.
CrossFit certified.

28:18.524 --> 28:20.043
Okay, okay, listen, listen!

28:20.906 --> 28:22.597
I just-- It's my fault.

28:22.701 --> 28:24.806
Not the kidnapping
and stuff,

28:24.910 --> 28:27.982
but, like, I said
some really mean stuff to her,
and I regret it,

28:28.085 --> 28:29.708
and I just need
to take it back.

28:29.811 --> 28:31.192
I called her a human mummy.

28:32.538 --> 28:33.953
Mummies are human.

28:34.609 --> 28:37.025
I'm aware of that now, yes.

28:37.129 --> 28:40.166
That is true.

28:40.270 --> 28:41.271
Please.

28:42.548 --> 28:45.240
All right, Alan,
I can't be responsible
for you.

28:46.207 --> 28:47.208
Okay. Yeah.

28:47.311 --> 28:50.280
I need you
to stay in the car.Yeah.

28:50.383 --> 28:52.489
In the car.In the car.

28:52.592 --> 28:55.043
The whole time.The whole time?

28:55.147 --> 28:56.389
Whole time.

28:56.493 --> 28:57.736
Mm-hmm.

28:59.496 --> 29:00.773
Yes!

29:07.711 --> 29:09.057
This is me.

29:09.955 --> 29:12.233
Really? Is this what
the SEAL teams use?

29:12.336 --> 29:14.994
"Only a fool chooses a horse
by its color."

29:15.098 --> 29:17.894
Right, right.
The Tao-te Ching?

29:17.997 --> 29:21.138
No, it was on the sign
back there at the rental place.

29:29.664 --> 29:30.872
Thank you.

29:35.428 --> 29:41.262
♪ I once had a life
Or rather, life had me♪

29:41.365 --> 29:44.368
♪ I was one among many♪

29:44.472 --> 29:47.924
♪ Or at least I seemed to be♪

29:48.027 --> 29:54.862
♪ Well, I read an old quotation
In a book just yesterday♪

29:54.965 --> 29:57.899
♪ Said
"Gonna reap just what you sow♪

29:58.003 --> 30:01.213
♪ The debts you make
You have to pay"♪

30:01.316 --> 30:03.042
♪ Can you get to that?♪

30:03.698 --> 30:05.148
What? What?

30:07.391 --> 30:09.393
I was hoping to invite you
to breakfast,

30:09.497 --> 30:12.155
but it looks like
you still have work to do.

30:13.121 --> 30:14.882
Uh, wait, wait, wait.

30:14.985 --> 30:16.504
Wait. Wait, wait, wait.

30:16.607 --> 30:18.609
I believe this says

30:18.713 --> 30:20.715
"rest" or "resting."

30:20.819 --> 30:23.718
So it would be,
"Kalaman and his treasure..."

30:23.822 --> 30:28.309
And then
there are some missing pieces,
and then "rest," "resting,"

30:28.412 --> 30:31.830
and something about
"tears," so...

30:33.624 --> 30:34.625
Resting where?

30:34.729 --> 30:35.937
Hmm? Oh!

30:36.041 --> 30:38.802
Didn't say.
It doesn't say.

30:40.148 --> 30:43.151
Miss Sage,
I need you to do better.

30:43.255 --> 30:46.706
Then next time
maybe don't kidnap
a romance novelist, hmm?

30:46.810 --> 30:49.019
My God,
this shouldn't be this hard!

30:49.123 --> 30:51.056
It is not some pauper's grave
we're looking for.

30:51.159 --> 30:53.437
It is a monument to a great man!

30:53.541 --> 30:55.474
King Kalaman was ambitious,
he was powerful,

30:55.577 --> 30:58.028
he was the first man
to build a city
in the Atlantic.

30:58.132 --> 31:00.789
The eyes of his subjects
would have turned to him.

31:00.893 --> 31:04.138
He would have had a pyramid,
a ziggurat, a tower

31:04.241 --> 31:06.209
to hold his Crown of Fire.

31:06.312 --> 31:09.212
All I need to know
is where it is.

31:09.315 --> 31:12.560
I don't know if you recall,
but you only said translate it.

31:12.663 --> 31:14.803
I-I translated it.

31:15.597 --> 31:17.185
Translate it again.

31:22.811 --> 31:25.849
One day, we're gonna
laugh about this.

31:25.953 --> 31:28.093
Such an adventure
we're having.

31:31.199 --> 31:35.548
I should go with you,
just for backup and awesomeness.

31:36.515 --> 31:38.172
This is pretty awesome.

31:38.275 --> 31:40.933
You got nature, the radio.

31:42.072 --> 31:45.696
Yeah, you're right,
but it's very, very important
to me

31:45.800 --> 31:47.664
that she knows
that I came to rescue her.

31:47.767 --> 31:49.459
Why?
Do you like this woman?

31:50.460 --> 31:52.669
No, I just brought snacks
and stuff.

31:52.772 --> 31:54.947
And she gets a little grumpy
when she's hungry.

31:55.051 --> 31:58.468
Blood pressure drops.
And I get that because I'm
a five-meal-a-day kind of guy.

31:58.571 --> 32:01.367
Do you keto, by the way?
You look like you keto.

32:01.471 --> 32:03.162
No.No. Yeah.

32:03.266 --> 32:04.992
You don't need it.

32:05.095 --> 32:06.579
What is it?

32:06.683 --> 32:10.273
I just want her to think of me
as more than a cover model.

32:10.376 --> 32:14.622
But, Alan,
you are so much more.
You're my lookout.

32:14.725 --> 32:18.074
Okay, can I at least do the part
where I put her in the car

32:18.177 --> 32:21.905
and I just go,
"Shh. You're safe now"?

32:22.975 --> 32:24.977
Sure, champ.
She'll love that.

32:25.081 --> 32:26.945
Oh, you're just going?
Going to start?

32:27.048 --> 32:29.464
You're starting
the mission now? Okay.

32:53.661 --> 32:55.870
Oh!

33:04.913 --> 33:06.398
Go to sleep.

33:06.501 --> 33:08.158
♪ Take a little walk
To the edge of town♪

33:08.262 --> 33:10.989
♪ And go across the tracks♪

33:12.335 --> 33:16.442
♪ Where the viaduct looms
Like a bird of doom♪

33:16.546 --> 33:20.653
♪ As it shifts and cracks♪

33:20.757 --> 33:26.521
♪ Where secrets lie
In the border fires
In the humming wires♪

33:26.625 --> 33:29.766
♪ Hey, man, you know
You're never coming back♪

33:29.869 --> 33:32.079
♪ Past the square
Past the bridge♪

33:32.182 --> 33:35.116
♪ Past the mills
Past the stacks♪

33:35.220 --> 33:36.359
Alan.What?

33:36.462 --> 33:38.223
This is a breach of trust, Alan.

33:38.326 --> 33:39.879
I can help. Let me help.

33:39.983 --> 33:43.159
♪ A tall handsome man
In a dusty black coat♪

33:43.262 --> 33:45.920
Stay close. Stay alive.

33:50.787 --> 33:52.030
Hey.

33:54.446 --> 33:56.862
♪ He'll wrap you in his arms♪

33:56.965 --> 33:58.484
Go to sleep.

33:58.588 --> 34:00.762
♪ Tell you that you've
Been a good boy♪

34:00.866 --> 34:04.973
I got his head.
What do I do with his head?
I'm just gonna set him down.

34:11.118 --> 34:12.326
No.

34:12.912 --> 34:14.086
Hey, hey, no!

34:14.190 --> 34:15.398
No, no, no!

34:17.055 --> 34:19.747
♪ There won't be a single thing
That you can do♪

34:19.850 --> 34:22.853
♪ He's a god, he's a man
He's a ghost, he's a guru♪

34:22.957 --> 34:24.786
Ooh, yeah! Ooh.

34:24.890 --> 34:25.856
Ow.

34:25.960 --> 34:27.513
Teamwork, yeah!

34:27.617 --> 34:30.896
Great effort, Alan, but that man
