I have an idea.

1:07:52.620 --> 1:07:54.070
We're gonna dig a hole,
throw our voices.

1:07:54.173 --> 1:07:56.106
"We're over here."
Can you sound like a bird?

1:07:56.210 --> 1:07:58.522
No, I have a plan.Alan, please, I'm thinking.

1:07:58.626 --> 1:08:02.319
I know, but I have a plan.Please, just let me think
about...

1:08:02.423 --> 1:08:06.047
Wait a minute.
They're shooting at you.Yeah, that's why we're hiding.

1:08:06.151 --> 1:08:08.463
No. No, no, no.
They're shooting only at you.

1:08:08.567 --> 1:08:11.087
They won't shoot me.
It's my brain that's valuable.

1:08:11.190 --> 1:08:15.056
What? I don't think
you actually hear the things
you say sometimes.

1:08:15.160 --> 1:08:17.852
Maybe I can shield you.You are not shielding me.

1:08:17.955 --> 1:08:20.199
I should be shielding you.Why? Because I'm a woman?

1:08:20.303 --> 1:08:23.375
That's supremely sexist.Well, look, I don't think
using women as human shields

1:08:23.478 --> 1:08:26.205
is exactly the change
that Gloria Seinfeld
had in mind, do you?

1:08:26.309 --> 1:08:29.139
Gloria Steinem?Whatever. Her too.
You know what? Fine.

1:08:29.243 --> 1:08:32.315
Please mansplain sexism
to me right now.Oh, my God. I am a woman.

1:08:32.418 --> 1:08:34.524
I can't mansplain anything.

1:08:34.627 --> 1:08:39.356
Uh, I'm a feminist,
and I think a woman can do
anything a man can do.

1:08:39.460 --> 1:08:41.910
We just need to stay here
until they get tired.I have an idea.

1:08:42.014 --> 1:08:43.705
Please can I tell you
my plan?Alan!

1:08:43.809 --> 1:08:47.123
This is not a situation
you can get out of
by ripping your shirt off.

1:08:47.226 --> 1:08:49.159
Not my shirt.

1:09:20.604 --> 1:09:21.916
Three!

1:09:22.019 --> 1:09:23.607
-Yes!
-Oh!

1:09:27.715 --> 1:09:29.579
Oh.

1:09:29.682 --> 1:09:32.927
That was different
than I had in my head.

1:09:33.030 --> 1:09:37.103
I just wanted us to stop them.Could it have been the wind
that made it do that?

1:09:37.207 --> 1:09:39.313
No, I think it was us.
I think... we did it.

1:09:39.416 --> 1:09:41.832
We did the one guy, right?
But that was, like--

1:09:41.936 --> 1:09:45.284
We just wanted him to stop.
But I think the other guy
could've moved, really.

1:09:45.388 --> 1:09:47.528
So, that was--
that one was on him.

1:09:47.631 --> 1:09:50.496
Even if we weren't here,
that could've happened.

1:09:50.600 --> 1:09:52.326
Why are you gonna stop
next to a cliff?

1:09:52.429 --> 1:09:54.880
They were wearing helmets,
so maybe they're...

1:09:54.983 --> 1:09:57.158
But the rest of their body
didn't have a helmet.

1:09:57.262 --> 1:09:58.470
So there'd just be a head.

1:09:58.573 --> 1:10:00.851
They were driving
recklessly, right?

1:10:00.955 --> 1:10:02.681
Don't be mean on a bike.

1:10:03.371 --> 1:10:05.131
Don't do mean stuff on a bike.

1:10:08.928 --> 1:10:11.172
I mean,
perhaps they're fine.

1:10:11.276 --> 1:10:13.692
Yeah, probably not.
But that's okay.

1:10:13.795 --> 1:10:18.075
That's all right.
You know, things happen.
Let's go.

1:10:20.285 --> 1:10:23.460
-You gonna put it back together?
-It's on loan.

1:10:36.266 --> 1:10:38.579
Look at me.Okay.

1:10:39.476 --> 1:10:41.513
What more can I do,
you know?

1:10:41.616 --> 1:10:43.549
You've done so much already,
Beth.

1:10:43.653 --> 1:10:46.690
My poor, sweet, little Nana
has lost her sight.

1:10:46.794 --> 1:10:49.521
The book release
is a complete disaster,

1:10:49.624 --> 1:10:51.281
which I've leveraged
everything on,

1:10:51.385 --> 1:10:53.732
so I'm probably,
most definitely
broke right now.

1:10:53.835 --> 1:10:57.080
And most importantly,
I've lost a writer.

1:10:57.183 --> 1:10:58.737
Who does that?
Who loses a writer?

1:10:58.840 --> 1:11:03.362
Okay, Beth, you remind me
of my best friend, Randy.

1:11:03.466 --> 1:11:05.951
Always looking out
for other people,

1:11:06.054 --> 1:11:08.402
never taking care of herself.

1:11:09.403 --> 1:11:10.818
Isn't that right, Randy?

1:11:13.338 --> 1:11:15.201
She's like my therapist,
this one over here.

1:11:15.305 --> 1:11:17.411
LOL. "Laughing Out Loud."

1:11:17.514 --> 1:11:19.482
After you take care
of your friend,

1:11:20.379 --> 1:11:21.725
how about we go to a beach?

1:11:21.829 --> 1:11:24.314
What?Look, I have a pickup
in Hawaii.

1:11:24.418 --> 1:11:26.385
She doesn't have to come.

1:11:26.489 --> 1:11:29.285
-Okay! Okay, you can come!

1:11:29.388 --> 1:11:31.390
She's hilarious.

1:11:32.184 --> 1:11:34.013
Let me ask you something.

1:11:34.117 --> 1:11:36.222
We're all sitting here
chitchatting,
but who's flying the plane?

1:11:36.326 --> 1:11:38.259
Autopilot.What?

1:11:38.363 --> 1:11:41.089
Sir, go to the cockpit,
fly the plane.

1:11:41.538 --> 1:11:42.539
Okay.

1:11:43.299 --> 1:11:45.059
I'm going to
go land the plane.

1:11:45.162 --> 1:11:46.612
Okay.

1:11:46.716 --> 1:11:48.614
No, no, no. Take the goat.
Please, take the goat.

1:11:48.718 --> 1:11:51.376
She's on break.
Enjoy the flight!

1:12:26.790 --> 1:12:28.136
Hi.Hola.

1:12:32.589 --> 1:12:35.281
This English dude came in
and basically kidnapped her.

1:12:37.422 --> 1:12:40.735
Hey, it's Beth.
Please leave a message,
and I'll get right back to you.

1:12:40.839 --> 1:12:43.704
Uh, hi, Beth.

1:12:43.807 --> 1:12:44.808
It's me.

1:12:44.912 --> 1:12:46.741
Uh, I'm alive!

1:12:47.466 --> 1:12:49.503
Uh, listen, um...

1:12:50.814 --> 1:12:51.850
Uh...

1:12:53.299 --> 1:12:57.407
I'm sorry that I
blew up the book tour.

1:12:57.511 --> 1:12:59.236
Um...

1:12:59.340 --> 1:13:01.722
I was just afraid

1:13:02.861 --> 1:13:04.518
and selfish. Uh--

1:13:04.621 --> 1:13:07.348
Oh, here comes Alan.
I'll call you back.

1:13:10.524 --> 1:13:13.527
So, uh, police
are searching for Fairfax,

1:13:13.630 --> 1:13:16.081
and they're gonna provide us
protection while we're here.

1:13:16.184 --> 1:13:18.014
Did they say
how long we'd be here?

1:13:18.117 --> 1:13:20.775
They're gonna try to get us
on a puddle jumper
later this evening.

1:13:20.879 --> 1:13:23.088
But, uh,
they said in the meantime,
the inn is really nice,

1:13:23.191 --> 1:13:25.780
and we can get cleaned up
and maybe a change of clothes.

1:13:25.884 --> 1:13:27.299
Okay.

1:13:30.751 --> 1:13:32.304
Okay. Yeah.

1:14:25.081 --> 1:14:26.531
Thank you.

1:14:27.117 --> 1:14:30.362
Come on.

1:14:30.466 --> 1:14:31.708
Dance with your husband.

1:14:31.812 --> 1:14:33.607
No, no, no.He's not my husband.

1:14:33.710 --> 1:14:35.436
It's okay.Dance with him.

1:14:35.540 --> 1:14:38.025
No, no. She doesn't want to.
She doesn't have
the right shoes.

1:14:38.128 --> 1:14:40.648
Actually, it's the only thing
these shoes are right for.

1:14:40.752 --> 1:14:42.995
You don't have to do this.

1:14:43.099 --> 1:14:44.859
It's okay. It's okay.

1:14:45.757 --> 1:14:46.723
Yeah?

1:16:05.353 --> 1:16:07.045
I wonder
what she's saying.

1:16:09.426 --> 1:16:10.911
It's folklore.

1:16:12.326 --> 1:16:14.362
Love song about a woman

1:16:14.466 --> 1:16:17.780
whose lover died,
and she didn't want to
leave his side.

1:16:18.815 --> 1:16:21.646
So she laid down
and refused to get up.

1:16:22.232 --> 1:16:23.993
Must be scary.

1:16:24.096 --> 1:16:27.997
Having to face your future
without the person
that you planned it with.

1:16:40.354 --> 1:16:41.907
What was that?

1:16:44.047 --> 1:16:47.706
Excuse me. Excuse me.
The, um-- the last line
that you sang.

1:16:47.810 --> 1:16:50.157
¿Quién llorará junto a mí?

1:16:53.091 --> 1:16:55.921
"The island will weep for me
in the well of endless tears."

1:16:56.025 --> 1:16:59.407
What is that,
the well of endless tears?
Is that a real place, or...

1:16:59.511 --> 1:17:01.133
Sinkhole place.

1:17:02.928 --> 1:17:04.654
Thank you. Gracias, gracias.

1:17:04.758 --> 1:17:06.829
Come here, come here.What is it?

1:17:08.451 --> 1:17:10.280
Hey, on the parchment,
it said,

1:17:10.384 --> 1:17:14.457
"King Kalaman
and his treasure laid to rest
in the well of endless tears."

1:17:14.560 --> 1:17:16.666
I thought
maybe it was a metaphor.

1:17:17.184 --> 1:17:18.737
It's not.

1:17:18.841 --> 1:17:21.706
The Well of Endless Tears
is a place.

1:17:21.809 --> 1:17:23.811
It's a sinkhole.

1:17:23.915 --> 1:17:26.089
There's a sinkhole
on the map.

1:17:27.435 --> 1:17:29.196
I think the tomb is there.

1:17:29.299 --> 1:17:31.681
This is so much better
than your books.What?

1:17:31.785 --> 1:17:33.269
There's like--
No, I don't mean any offense.

1:17:33.372 --> 1:17:35.271
I'm kidding. I'm kidding.It's, like, equal.

1:17:35.374 --> 1:17:37.583
I'm kidding. I'm kidding.Look at you.
You want to go there.

1:17:37.687 --> 1:17:39.551
What? No.I can see. Yes, you do.

1:17:39.655 --> 1:17:42.761
That would be insane.
That would be insane.
I just-- I just--

1:17:42.865 --> 1:17:47.248
It's just that
we're so close to it,
but, you know, we can't--

1:17:47.352 --> 1:17:48.664
No.

1:17:48.767 --> 1:17:51.459
This is your story.
How do you want to write it?

1:17:52.253 --> 1:17:54.566
I'd like to know
that it's there,

1:17:54.670 --> 1:17:56.326
that all this
meant something.

1:17:56.430 --> 1:17:58.294
Okay. Then let's go.

1:17:58.397 --> 1:18:00.261
We'll stay one more day.
As soon as the sun's up,

1:18:00.365 --> 1:18:02.125
we're gonna go find
the Well of Endless Tears.

1:18:02.229 --> 1:18:05.094
But what if it's nothing?So what? Then we say we tried.

1:18:05.197 --> 1:18:06.440
And Fairfax?

1:18:06.543 --> 1:18:08.960
The cops are after Fairfax.
Don't worry about him.

1:18:10.064 --> 1:18:10.858
This is crazy.

1:18:10.962 --> 1:18:12.653
Yeah, but look at you.What?

1:18:12.757 --> 1:18:15.725
It's the very first time
I've ever seen you
totally unafraid.

1:18:16.346 --> 1:18:18.072
And alive.

1:18:18.176 --> 1:18:20.696
I'm gonna go tell them
our plans have changed
and find us a ride.

1:18:20.799 --> 1:18:22.249
Where are you going?

1:18:25.908 --> 1:18:27.979
I see you met
my friend here.

1:18:28.082 --> 1:18:32.466
He told me you were just
about to jump on a plane,

1:18:32.569 --> 1:18:35.020
without so much as
saying goodbye.

1:18:35.124 --> 1:18:38.541
I said, "No way.
Not my Loretta.

1:18:38.644 --> 1:18:43.097
Not when she's the only one
who can lead me to the tomb."

1:18:46.514 --> 1:18:48.585
Stop squeezing so hard.

1:18:49.414 --> 1:18:52.210
Ow. Get your hands off of me!

1:18:53.073 --> 1:18:54.937
Ow! Let go!

1:18:55.420 --> 1:18:56.628
I-I need a car.

1:18:56.732 --> 1:18:58.664
A car, an auto.
Does anybody have an auto?

1:19:07.156 --> 1:19:08.226
No, no. No.

1:19:08.951 --> 1:19:10.262
I-I-I need an auto.

1:19:10.366 --> 1:19:11.712
I'll trade you my watch.

1:19:11.816 --> 1:19:13.231
It's a really expensive watch.
Do you have a car?

1:19:13.334 --> 1:19:14.853
It's a Bulgari.
This thing glows in the dark.

1:19:14.957 --> 1:19:16.752
It's waterproof.I have motorcycle.

1:19:30.351 --> 1:19:32.112
Cool, isn't it?

1:19:32.215 --> 1:19:35.322
I always thought,
why can't your personal tank
also have a minibar?

1:19:35.425 --> 1:19:36.910
Have a drink.

1:19:37.013 --> 1:19:38.566
Do you mind?

1:19:38.670 --> 1:19:40.085
Uh, yes.

1:19:40.189 --> 1:19:42.329
He has a bit of a grudge
against you, I'm afraid.

1:19:42.432 --> 1:19:45.228
Something about
a motorbike accident
his friends had?

1:19:45.332 --> 1:19:46.505
Why are you doing this?

1:19:46.609 --> 1:19:48.369
I want something
nobody else has.

1:19:49.267 --> 1:19:51.096
When my father gifted--

1:19:54.168 --> 1:19:55.687
As I was saying,

1:19:55.791 --> 1:19:58.724
when my father gifted
his empire

1:19:58.828 --> 1:20:01.279
-to my baby brother--

1:20:08.320 --> 1:20:09.839
Who is that?

1:20:18.572 --> 1:20:20.781
Is that a Ken doll
on a moped?

1:20:21.575 --> 1:20:23.094
I know him from somewhere.

1:20:23.197 --> 1:20:24.854
Oh, I-I-I doubt that.

1:20:24.958 --> 1:20:27.167
Because what
you are looking at

1:20:27.270 --> 1:20:30.170
is a highly trained
combat specialist,

1:20:30.273 --> 1:20:33.863
forged in the furnaces
of Afghanistan, Iraq,

1:20:33.967 --> 1:20:36.555
Kuwait, Sa-- Sarasota...

1:20:36.659 --> 1:20:38.730
Incredible skin.
No eczema problems.

1:20:38.834 --> 1:20:42.527
And he will not stop
until I am safe!

1:20:42.630 --> 1:20:44.840
So you pull
this space tank over,

1:20:44.943 --> 1:20:48.084
unless you would like to perish
like his friends did.

1:20:48.188 --> 1:20:51.605
And he is responsible
for their perishment.

1:20:51.708 --> 1:20:54.401
He might not have meant to,

1:20:54.504 --> 1:20:57.783
but they... perished, so...

1:21:12.729 --> 1:21:13.972
Okay, who-who is this?

1:21:14.076 --> 1:21:15.974
I have seen him
somewhere before.

1:21:18.459 --> 1:21:19.702
No, no, no.

1:21:19.805 --> 1:21:21.531
That's your cover model,
isn't it?

1:21:21.635 --> 1:21:23.913
Yes. I knew
I knew him from somewhere.

1:21:24.810 --> 1:21:25.881
Get up there.

1:21:25.984 --> 1:21:27.365
And kill him creatively.

1:21:27.468 --> 1:21:29.574
I love watching hunks fail.

1:21:31.921 --> 1:21:34.165
I guess I-I will
have that drink.

1:21:35.856 --> 1:21:37.133
Oh, shit.

1:21:37.237 --> 1:21:39.791
Is it okay
if I just top 'er off?

1:21:39.895 --> 1:21:41.068
Yeah, that's fine, but--

1:21:41.172 --> 1:21:43.139
Oh, my God,
have you used a glass before?

1:21:43.243 --> 1:21:44.589
Sorry.

1:21:44.692 --> 1:21:46.177
What would
Jack Trainer do?

1:21:48.386 --> 1:21:49.456
It's hot in here.

1:21:49.559 --> 1:21:52.562
Anyone else feeling
how hot it is?

1:21:52.666 --> 1:21:53.736
Are you trying to be sexy?

1:21:53.839 --> 1:21:55.634
This is very weird.
Please, stop.

1:21:55.738 --> 1:21:57.636
I could set your world
on fire.

1:22:08.233 --> 1:22:10.546
Go to sleep! Go to sleep!

1:22:10.649 --> 1:22:12.375
Go to sleep! Sleep!

1:22:14.791 --> 1:22:16.621
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

1:22:16.724 --> 1:22:18.002
Time-out.

1:22:18.105 --> 1:22:19.037
Time-in!

1:22:24.870 --> 1:22:27.701
No! Don't shoot her!
I need her!

1:22:29.358 --> 1:22:31.222
Oh, Jesus!

1:22:31.325 --> 1:22:32.740
Ow, ow, ow.

1:22:36.675 --> 1:22:39.092
Move your foot! Move your foot!

1:22:42.164 --> 1:22:44.373
-Go to sleep, asshole.

1:22:44.476 --> 1:22:46.133
Get out there! Look!

1:22:50.724 --> 1:22:52.036
A bigger guy?

1:22:52.139 --> 1:22:53.347
Oh, no.

1:22:54.693 --> 1:22:55.936
What?

1:22:58.421 --> 1:22:59.353
Move it!

1:23:01.079 --> 1:23:03.392
No, no, no. No, no, no.

1:23:04.289 --> 1:23:06.188
Hey! Get in.

1:23:06.705 --> 1:23:07.810
Him or me?

1:23:11.917 --> 1:23:16.715
This is not one of
your cheap, vapid
lady-fantasy books, Loretta.

1:23:16.819 --> 1:23:18.786
This is real life.

1:23:19.718 --> 1:23:21.582
And we will kill him.

1:23:21.686 --> 1:23:23.412
Tell us where the tomb is.

1:23:38.082 --> 1:23:39.393
Hi.
So, whoever's in charge,

1:23:39.497 --> 1:23:42.120
I need you to send
officials to go here.

1:23:42.224 --> 1:23:43.328
Here.

1:23:44.467 --> 1:23:46.297
We are closed.

1:23:46.400 --> 1:23:47.746
You're closed?

1:23:49.679 --> 1:23:52.786
You know I've been
trying to take a nap
for a year and a half?

1:23:52.889 --> 1:23:54.443
A year and a half.

1:23:55.375 --> 1:23:58.481
I have been burning the candle
at both ends,

1:23:58.585 --> 1:23:59.931
the midnight oil,

1:24:00.035 --> 1:24:03.003
since way before
my friend got kidnapped.

1:24:03.107 --> 1:24:04.970
And all I want to do

1:24:05.523 --> 1:24:07.663
is kick my feet back

1:24:07.766 --> 1:24:09.009
and drink some wine

1:24:09.113 --> 1:24:11.494
that I'm probably
too tired to drink.

1:24:11.598 --> 1:24:13.531
And I want a massage.

1:24:13.634 --> 1:24:18.294
I want someone to massage
my shoulders and my feet,

1:24:18.398 --> 1:24:20.434
and I want it at the same time.

1:24:20.538 --> 1:24:24.231
And I don't care if logistically
that doesn't make sense.

1:24:24.335 --> 1:24:26.992
Because I have worked hard.

1:24:27.855 --> 1:24:30.306
The same way that
I know that you have.

1:24:31.204 --> 1:24:33.413
So I hate to ask you

1:24:33.516 --> 1:24:35.898
to leave this place open
a few more minutes,

1:24:36.001 --> 1:24:37.934
because if we don't,

1:24:38.038 --> 1:24:41.593
a very close friend of mine
and her cover model

1:24:41.697 --> 1:24:43.457
are going to die.

1:25:06.308 --> 1:25:07.861
No good way in, boss!

1:25:07.964 --> 1:25:10.105
What about the caves?

1:25:10.864 --> 1:25:12.210
That's too dangerous!

1:25:12.314 --> 1:25:15.317
Well,
we'll be very careful then.

1:25:28.882 --> 1:25:30.194
Well, come on!

1:25:34.888 --> 1:25:36.717
This way.I have a rule about

1:25:36.821 --> 1:25:38.340
not going into
super creepy caves.

1:25:49.696 --> 1:25:52.630
Julian?
His name is Julian?

1:25:52.733 --> 1:25:55.598
He seems more like
a Buck or a Bruce.

1:25:55.702 --> 1:25:57.186
Lead the way.

1:26:00.879 --> 1:26:03.261
Go on. Don't be scared.

1:26:33.015 --> 1:26:34.810
Watch your step there.

1:26:34.913 --> 1:26:36.087
Bruce!

1:26:36.191 --> 1:26:37.192
Julian. Oh, no!Julian!

1:26:37.295 --> 1:26:38.917
Whoa.

1:26:39.021 --> 1:26:40.540
Whoa.

1:26:41.196 --> 1:26:42.680
